1. About this Addendum
This Addendum will help you better understand the following:
Definitions;
Personal Information we Process;
Our legal bases for Processing;
Transfer to third parties;
Storage of Personal Information;
Security of Personal Information;
How we use Cookies;
Your Data Subject rights;
How to contact us; and
Changes to this Addendum.
We understand the importance of your Personal Information to you and will do our best to ensure the security and reliability of your Personal Information. We are committed to maintaining your trust in us and Processing your Personal Information in accordance with principles of lawfulness, legitimacy, necessity, and good faith, and not acting in any manner that is misleading, fraudulent, or coercive.
We also take security measures to protect your Personal Information in accordance with mature industry standards.
2. Deffinitions
For the purposes of this Addendum only, except as otherwise provided in the context:
2.1
"
Personal Information
" or "
PI
" refers to any kind of information related to an identified or identifiable natural person as electronically or otherwise recorded, excluding information that has been anonymized.
2.2.
"
Sensitive Personal Information
" or "
Sensitive PI
" refers to Personal Information that, once leaked or illegally used, will easily lead to the infringement of human dignity or harm to the personal or property safety of a natural person, including biometric recognition, religious belief, specific identity, medical and health condition, financial account, personal location tracking and other information of a natural person, as well as any Personal Information of a minor under the age of 14.
2.3
"
Process
", "
Processed
", or "
Processing
" includes the collection, storage, use, editing, transfer, provision, disclosure, and deletion of Personal Information.
2.4
"
Data Subject
" refers to the natural person identified by or associated with Personal Information.
2.5
"
Personal Information Processor
" refers to any organization or individual that independently determines the purpose and method of Processing in their Personal Information Processing activities and provides Personal Information to a recipient outside the territory of China.
2.6
"
Entrusted Processor
" refers to any organization or individual that Processes Personal Information on behalf of a Personal Information Processor.
2.7
"
Overseas Recipient
" refers to an organization or individual located outside the territory of China that receives Personal Information from the Personal Information Processor.
2.8
"
Regulatory Authority
" refers to the cyberspace administration department of China at or above the provincial level.
2.9
"
Relevant Laws and Regulations
" refers to the Cybersecurity Law of the People's Republic of China, the Data Security Law of the People's Republic of China, the Personal Information Protection Law of the People's Republic of China, the Civil Code of the People's Republic of China, and other applicable laws and regulations of the People's Republic of China.
2.10
The meanings of undefined terms in this Addendum are the same as those stipulated in Relevant Laws and Regulations.
