3.2. How we collect and use the Personal Information of Minors
Our services are not intended for or targeted to the use of children under the age of 14, and we do not knowingly collect any Personal Information from such children. If you believe we have received Personal Information from a child under the age of 14, please contact us so that we can delete the information immediately.
4. Our legal bases for Processing
Infineon Processes your Personal Information:
where it is necessary for the conclusion or performance of a contract to which you are a contracting party;
where it is necessary for performing a statutory responsibility or statutory obligation;
where it is necessary for responding to a public health emergency or for protecting the life, health, or property of a natural person in an emergency;
where Personal Information, which has already been disclosed by you or otherwise legally disclosed, is Processed within a reasonable scope and in accordance with Relevant Laws and Regulations;
where it is necessary for carrying out human resources management under employment policies legally established or a collective contract legally concluded;
with your consent; or
under any other circumstance as provided by Relevant Laws and Regulations.
Sometimes we might need to collect your separate consent for Processing activities if required by Relevant Laws and Regulations. We will notify you if such separate consent is required and provide details about the Processing.
5. Transfers to third parties
We may need to transfer your Personal Information to other Infineon Group entities or third parties, especially to selected Entrusted Processors, distributors, partners, and sales representatives.
We conduct Personal Information protection impact assessments before transferring your Personal Information to third parties.
5.1. Entrusted Processors
We may transfer your Personal Information to our Entrusted Processors that need to know such information to fulfil one or more of the
"Purposes of Processing PI"
described in Section 3.1, such as our professional advisors and technology service providers. When we share your Personal Information with Entrusted Processors, we require them to:
process Personal Information only as we instruct them;
not transfer your Personal Information to other parties without our approval;
implement adequate operational, technical, and organizational security measures to protect your Personal Information from any unauthorized access, leakage, tampering, or loss;
keep your Personal Information confidential;
return or delete your Personal Information at our instruction;
submit to our supervision; and
act in a manner consistent with Infineon policies and Relevant Laws and Regulations.
